1
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:11,533
<i> We need to recoup our losses</i>

2
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:13,733
<i> by acquiring Paradiso Escaño.</i>

3
00:00:13,867 --> 00:00:15,133
<i> If you really want that deal,</i>

4
00:00:15,267 --> 00:00:16,633
<i> you better impress me.</i>

5
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:17,967
<i> I can close that deal, Dad.</i>

6
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:19,433
<i> In your dreams, Edward.</i>

7
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:20,400
<i> What is this?</i>

8
00:00:20,533 --> 00:00:22,100
<i>Are you letting him fool you
again?</i>

9
00:00:22,233 --> 00:00:24,233
<i> Your dad has changed.</i>

10
00:00:24,367 --> 00:00:27,133
<i>Have you forgotten
what he did to you?</i>

11
00:00:27,267 --> 00:00:29,133
<i>- Let go of me.
- Please, let's reconcile.</i>

12
00:00:29,267 --> 00:00:30,667
<i>- What?
- I'll leave my family</i>

13
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:31,967
<i>if that's what it takes for you
to give me another chance.</i>

14
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:33,267
<i>She already said she doesn't
want to talk to you.</i>

15
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:34,233
<i>Is this who you replaced me
with?</i>

16
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:35,500
<i> You're lucky, Sir.</i>

17
00:00:35,633 --> 00:00:37,033
<i> You found "the one."</i>

18
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:38,333
<i> Everyone has a perfect match.</i>

19
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:39,767
<i> So open your eyes.</i>

20
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,067
<i> You never know.</i>

21
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,167
<i>The woman meant for you might
already be right there.</i>

22
00:00:47,933 --> 00:00:49,100
Excuse me, Sir.

23
00:00:49,233 --> 00:00:50,433
Angeline is acting up.

24
00:00:50,567 --> 00:00:52,067
- What?
- Over here, sir.

25
00:00:56,167 --> 00:01:00,833
She's hurting the plants!

26
00:01:00,967 --> 00:01:03,767
She's hurting the plants!

27
00:01:03,900 --> 00:01:05,667
They're getting hurt!

28
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:07,533
They're are in pain.

29
00:01:09,433 --> 00:01:11,933
Sweetheart,
sweetheart.

30
00:01:12,067 --> 00:01:13,100
Calm down, sweetheart.

31
00:01:13,233 --> 00:01:14,300
The plants are fine.

32
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:15,733
We'll just replace the base.

33
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:17,300
Okay? Calm down.

34
00:01:17,433 --> 00:01:18,933
The plants are okay.

35
00:01:19,067 --> 00:01:20,567
They're not hurt.

36
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:23,067
No.

37
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,800
I know what to do.

38
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:32,567
Sir Escaño, may I?

39
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,000
Thank you very much,
Ms. Castillo.

40
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:06,500
You have a good one over here,
Mr. Torrecampo.

41
00:02:07,533 --> 00:02:09,700
Don't ever let her go.

42
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,367
Everybody...

43
00:02:15,533 --> 00:02:16,800
Listen up.

44
00:02:19,667 --> 00:02:23,933
I have decided
who will be the exclusive

45
00:02:24,067 --> 00:02:27,500
realty partner
of Paradiso Escaño.

46
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,500
None other than...

47
00:02:35,633 --> 00:02:37,967
the Torrecampo Realty.

48
00:02:43,967 --> 00:02:46,367
I want people I can trust.

49
00:02:49,033 --> 00:02:50,567
People with compassion.

50
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:58,867
And that's exactly
what Ms. Castillo showed today.

51
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:02,667
So congratulations.

52
00:03:05,067 --> 00:03:07,067
Sir...

53
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,833
is this really final?

54
00:03:08,967 --> 00:03:11,000
Do you still want me
to reconsider?

55
00:03:11,133 --> 00:03:12,133
No! No, Sir.

56
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:13,067
We'll take it po.

57
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,133
- We'll take it, thank you.
- Okay.

58
00:03:14,267 --> 00:03:15,800
- Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

59
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:18,833
Congratulations again.

60
00:03:18,967 --> 00:03:21,233
See you later
for the contract signing.

61
00:03:22,567 --> 00:03:25,633
Please, everybody...

62
00:03:25,767 --> 00:03:28,867
enjoy tonight's festivities.

63
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,500
- Thank you so much, Sir.
- Okay.

64
00:03:30,633 --> 00:03:31,933
- Thank you.
- Okay.

65
00:03:32,067 --> 00:03:33,600
Please, excuse us.

66
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:42,067
We did it!

67
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:52,733
This is all because of you.

68
00:03:52,867 --> 00:03:55,900
Didn't I tell you
you're my lucky charm?

69
00:03:58,633 --> 00:03:59,867
You were amazing.

70
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:58,767
I'm sure Dad will be happy
about this.

71
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,600
He did send the right people.

72
00:05:02,833 --> 00:05:07,200
Of course, it was Ms. Castillo
who convinced me

73
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:09,033
to take you on.

74
00:05:09,167 --> 00:05:11,133
You must be very proud of her.

75
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:13,767
I am.

76
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:15,933
Honestly, I'm glad I got to be

77
00:05:16,067 --> 00:05:17,400
on this trip with her.

78
00:05:18,633 --> 00:05:21,067
I got to know her better.

79
00:05:27,933 --> 00:05:29,700
Why was she chosen anyway?

80
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:34,333
Didn't Mr. Escaño know
about her viral scandal?

81
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,633
Oh, my god.

82
00:05:35,767 --> 00:05:38,733
She's the mistress who got
confronted by the wife, right?

83
00:05:38,867 --> 00:05:39,833
That's right.

84
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:43,500
That's probably why she went
back to Batangas.

85
00:05:43,633 --> 00:05:46,633
- OMG, that's true.
- She's shameless.

86
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:53,867
How can you close deals
if all you do is gossip?

87
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:58,767
Let me make this clear,
I'm here for business.

88
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:01,167
And Randall and I have been
separated for a long time.

89
00:06:02,733 --> 00:06:04,867
- Girl, let's go.
- Come on.

90
00:06:08,667 --> 00:06:10,933
Hey! Liar!

91
00:06:11,067 --> 00:06:14,967
I don't believe you
and my husband really broke up!

92
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:18,000
Randall left us because of you!

93
00:06:18,133 --> 00:06:20,467
My children no longer
have a father!

94
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,600
Why did you even come back here?

95
00:06:22,733 --> 00:06:24,833
Why did you go after
my husband again?

96
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:27,867
No! I'm not getting back
together with him!

97
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,767
Yes, he came to see me,
but I rejected him!

98
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:33,100
Then explain this!

99
00:06:33,233 --> 00:06:36,900
This was sent to me
by an agent I know!

100
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:39,800
So stop pretending, okay?

101
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:41,533
Jenny, you're hurting me.

102
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:42,667
That's enough.

103
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,900
That's nothing compared
to what you did to us!

104
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:47,200
My husband left us!

105
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:50,467
This woman is my husband's
mistress!

106
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:53,200
She destroyed our family!

107
00:06:59,233 --> 00:07:00,800
Excuse me, Mr. Torrecampo.

108
00:07:00,933 --> 00:07:02,833
Someone's attacking
Ms. Castillo.

109
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:11,133
You're misunderstanding
that photo!

110
00:07:11,267 --> 00:07:13,067
Ask Randall yourself!

111
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,400
Liar!

112
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:16,567
Don't make a fool out of me!

113
00:07:16,700 --> 00:07:20,533
Jenny, I ended things with him

114
00:07:20,667 --> 00:07:23,733
the moment I found out
he had a wife and kids!

115
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:27,233
I swore to myself
I'd forget him!

116
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:28,700
Liar!

117
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:32,733
You didn't care
if our family was destroyed

118
00:07:32,867 --> 00:07:34,800
as long as you got my husband!

119
00:07:34,933 --> 00:07:37,767
Why are you blaming me?

120
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:39,233
I rejected him!

121
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:41,833
It's not my fault
he still left you!

122
00:07:41,967 --> 00:07:42,933
It's that so?

123
00:07:44,567 --> 00:07:46,433
- Enough! Stop this!
- Hey!

124
00:07:46,567 --> 00:07:47,367
What are you doing?

125
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:48,300
You're butting in!

126
00:07:48,467 --> 00:07:49,400
Are you trying to impress Marj?

127
00:07:49,533 --> 00:07:50,333
Me butting in?

128
00:07:50,467 --> 00:07:51,400
Control your wife!

129
00:07:51,533 --> 00:07:52,600
She's causing a scene!

130
00:07:52,733 --> 00:07:53,333
You've got some nerve!

131
00:07:53,467 --> 00:07:56,333
Jenny, stop it!

132
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:58,633
Leave Marj alone!

133
00:07:58,767 --> 00:07:59,933
Leave her alone!

134
00:08:00,067 --> 00:08:00,733
She doesn't want you anymore!

135
00:08:00,867 --> 00:08:02,800
Don't you get it?

136
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:16,333
Enough!

137
00:08:17,367 --> 00:08:18,667
Get them out!

138
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,900
Out!

139
00:08:24,933 --> 00:08:28,467
- Get them out!
- Ma'am, please come out now.

140
00:08:30,067 --> 00:08:31,433
Marj, are you okay?

141
00:08:31,567 --> 00:08:32,467
Do you want me to take you
to the hospital?

142
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,467
- Come on.
- No, no, no.

143
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:34,800
I'm fine.

144
00:08:34,933 --> 00:08:36,467
- I'm really fine.
- Are you sure?

145
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:40,700
Don't worry about that crazy
couple anymore, okay?

146
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:41,767
Okay?

147
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:43,700
They won't bother you again.

148
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:46,033
And if they ever come after you,

149
00:08:46,167 --> 00:08:47,400
I've got you, all right?

150
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:14,967
Jobert.

151
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,833
Mom has to go out
for a bit, okay?

152
00:09:17,967 --> 00:09:19,733
I'll be back soon.

153
00:09:21,567 --> 00:09:23,633
I'll come with you.

154
00:09:23,767 --> 00:09:26,500
No, sweetheart,
no, you can't.

155
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:27,567
No, you can't.

156
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:30,200
You can't come with me
where I'm going, son.

157
00:09:30,367 --> 00:09:33,000
And look, your food's
already on the table.

158
00:09:34,033 --> 00:09:36,500
Hannah will be back later.

159
00:09:37,867 --> 00:09:39,733
Where are you going?

160
00:09:41,367 --> 00:09:43,533
That's not important,
sweetheart.

161
00:09:45,267 --> 00:09:49,567
When your sister calls...

162
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,267
promise me...

163
00:09:55,267 --> 00:09:57,067
you won't tell her
anything, okay?

164
00:09:58,567 --> 00:10:01,467
Ah, It's our little secret,
all right?

165
00:10:02,467 --> 00:10:04,633
You really shouldn't have
stepped in earlier.

166
00:10:04,767 --> 00:10:06,467
Look, you got dragged into it.

167
00:10:07,533 --> 00:10:08,900
You're welcome, huh?

168
00:10:10,167 --> 00:10:11,733
Okay, I'm sorry.

169
00:10:11,867 --> 00:10:12,800
Thank you.

170
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:14,500
I mean, if things got worse,

171
00:10:14,633 --> 00:10:16,467
how was I supposed
to get you home alive?

172
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:19,100
Well...

173
00:10:19,233 --> 00:10:21,333
you won't find
anyone else like me.

174
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:26,200
What happened?

175
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:28,300
- What happened?
- Ouch!

176
00:10:28,433 --> 00:10:32,133
Looks like it got hit earlier.

177
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:34,400
That's okay now.

178
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:35,433
- It hurts, ouch!
- Oh my, Sir,

179
00:10:35,567 --> 00:10:37,700
it looks like
your shoulder's dislocated.

180
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:40,967
It hurts.

181
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,767
And the hospital's
pretty far from here.

182
00:10:51,167 --> 00:10:55,800
You said it's bad
to keep secrets.

183
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,800
This is different, sweetheart.

184
00:10:59,933 --> 00:11:02,367
And Mom really has to do this.

185
00:11:03,733 --> 00:11:07,167
Besides, do you want

186
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:09,500
your sister to get mad at me?

187
00:11:09,667 --> 00:11:11,900
You don't like it
when we fight, right?

188
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,267
No.

189
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:16,700
No fighting, Mom.

190
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:21,833
I don't want you
and Marj fighting.

191
00:11:31,967 --> 00:11:33,233
Jobert.

192
00:11:33,367 --> 00:11:35,067
Jobert, listen to Mom.

193
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:38,300
I'm leaving for a bit.

194
00:11:38,433 --> 00:11:39,600
You stay here.

195
00:11:41,433 --> 00:11:43,200
Play with Pong.

196
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:46,133
I'll be back soon, okay?

197
00:11:46,267 --> 00:11:48,233
Don't go anywhere, son.

198
00:11:48,367 --> 00:11:49,567
Promise me.

199
00:12:10,733 --> 00:12:12,633
Oh my god...

200
00:12:12,767 --> 00:12:14,333
This is exactly
what I was afraid of.

201
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,300
- Hey!
- Hey, don't panic.

202
00:12:16,433 --> 00:12:17,600
Just chill, okay?

203
00:12:17,733 --> 00:12:18,600
Just chill, you've got this.

204
00:12:18,733 --> 00:12:19,667
You're Miss Tough Girl,
remember?

205
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,067
- You can do it.
- It's far from anything vital,

206
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,400
but you can't even look

207
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:23,833
- at your shoulder.
- Yes.

208
00:12:23,967 --> 00:12:25,200
Gosh, I'm serious, Paolo.

209
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:28,100
This is my fault.

210
00:12:28,233 --> 00:12:29,767
Oh, can I...

211
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:32,433
When Jobert gets like this,
I do something.

212
00:12:32,567 --> 00:12:33,467
Can I try it on you?

213
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:35,200
All right.

214
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:36,733
- Ah!
- Hey, wait!

215
00:12:36,867 --> 00:12:38,467
Don't panic.

216
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,467
Okay, here we go.

217
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,233
There.

218
00:12:40,367 --> 00:12:42,067
Okay, take a deep breath.

219
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,467
I'll rotate it three times.

220
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:48,133
One, two...

221
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:49,400
Three!

222
00:12:49,533 --> 00:12:51,233
What?

223
00:12:51,367 --> 00:12:52,367
How is it?

224
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,500
Did it get worse?

225
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:57,133
Actually, it feels better.

226
00:12:57,267 --> 00:12:59,000
Yes, much better.

227
00:12:59,133 --> 00:13:00,900
Can you take off your polo?

228
00:13:01,033 --> 00:13:04,167
I need to wrap this around
your shoulder.

229
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:09,600
I'll do it,
I'll help you.

230
00:13:09,733 --> 00:13:12,000
I thought you said it was far
from anything vital?

231
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:14,633
It is far from anything vital.

232
00:13:14,767 --> 00:13:16,133
But it still hurts.

233
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,033
At least you know.

234
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:49,333
It hurts, right?

235
00:14:00,900 --> 00:14:03,100
Why is your hand shaking?

236
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:06,367
Just relax. Are you getting
distracted by how good I look?

237
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:09,467
- Whatever.
- Oh!

238
00:14:22,467 --> 00:14:24,267
Why are you staring at me?

239
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:26,833
You think I'm pretty, don't you?

240
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,133
I was just going to invite you
to celebrate.

241
00:14:29,267 --> 00:14:30,500
Let's drink.

242
00:14:30,633 --> 00:14:31,833
It'll help with the pain.

243
00:14:31,967 --> 00:14:33,267
Now is the time to let loose.

244
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:34,967
To wash away all the bitterness.

245
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:38,167
Sorry, but I really
don't want to.

246
00:14:40,833 --> 00:14:42,067
Darn him.

247
00:14:43,867 --> 00:14:47,633
I took care of my family
my whole life.

248
00:14:48,767 --> 00:14:53,933
I had to be both mom and dad
when my father left us.

249
00:14:55,633 --> 00:14:59,067
Everything I do
is for my family.

250
00:15:02,367 --> 00:15:05,533
I only let myself be happy once.

251
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:07,800
To love.

252
00:15:11,867 --> 00:15:13,967
And I loved the wrong person.

253
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,600
Don't be too hard on yourself.

254
00:15:20,733 --> 00:15:22,200
You didn't know.

255
00:15:25,233 --> 00:15:27,533
I want to be like you.

256
00:15:27,667 --> 00:15:29,467
Someone...

257
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,033
Someone who doesn't
think too much.

258
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:33,200
Someone who doesn't have
to be serious.

259
00:15:33,333 --> 00:15:34,233
You know?

260
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:37,100
Someone who only thinks
about fun.

261
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:41,900
But I can't.

262
00:15:45,533 --> 00:15:48,200
I can't, I can't.

263
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:51,400
That kind of life isn't for me.

264
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:55,000
I can't, I can't.

265
00:15:58,067 --> 00:16:00,067
I can't.

266
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,367
I can't.

267
00:16:14,767 --> 00:16:16,633
Teach me how to be like you.

268
00:16:20,067 --> 00:16:21,267
Come on.

269
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:23,600
Please.

270
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:31,100
Marj...

271
00:16:31,233 --> 00:16:32,767
you're better the way you are.

272
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:34,667
Don't copy me, okay?

273
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,967
I like you better
as Miss Tough Girl.

274
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:38,533
Kind.

275
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:40,033
Strong.

276
00:16:40,167 --> 00:16:41,367
Thoughtful.

277
00:16:42,467 --> 00:16:43,600
Don't be like me.

278
00:16:43,733 --> 00:16:44,933
You are thoughtful.

279
00:16:45,967 --> 00:16:47,633
Yes.

280
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:52,100
You help me even
when I don't ask for help.

281
00:16:52,233 --> 00:16:57,900
And Jobert calls you
"Kind Big Brother".

282
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:02,033
Come on.

283
00:17:02,167 --> 00:17:03,500
Teach me.

284
00:17:03,633 --> 00:17:05,200
I want to be like you.

285
00:17:11,967 --> 00:17:13,500
No, I can do it.

286
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:14,567
No.

287
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:17,600
I can be dense like you.

288
00:17:18,867 --> 00:17:19,933
Come on.

289
00:17:20,067 --> 00:17:22,700
I want to learn

290
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,900
how not to care about
what I feel

291
00:17:25,033 --> 00:17:26,433
or what other people say.

292
00:17:27,967 --> 00:17:31,000
I still care about
how people feel.

293
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:39,867
Your phone.

294
00:17:43,067 --> 00:17:43,800
Hello?

295
00:17:43,933 --> 00:17:45,233
<i> Hello, Marj?</i>

296
00:17:45,367 --> 00:17:46,933
Marj? How are you there?

297
00:17:47,067 --> 00:17:48,333
Thank you.

298
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:49,800
<i> Edward!</i>

299
00:17:49,933 --> 00:17:51,533
How are you?

300
00:17:51,667 --> 00:17:53,933
Ah! I missed you!

301
00:17:54,067 --> 00:17:56,667
You missed
all the action earlier!

302
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,367
<i> Marj?</i>

303
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:00,100
Have you been drinking?

304
00:18:00,233 --> 00:18:01,267
Edward!

305
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:02,333
Come on.

306
00:18:02,467 --> 00:18:03,567
<i> You had enough.</i>

307
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:04,967
<i> You're drunk.</i>

308
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:05,933
<i>- I'm taking you to your room.
- No! Wait! Wait!</i>

309
00:18:06,067 --> 00:18:07,400
<i>- I'm not drunk yet!
- Paolo?</i>

310
00:18:07,533 --> 00:18:08,633
I still want to drink!

311
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:10,333
I wanna be free.

312
00:18:10,733 --> 00:18:12,400
Marj, you've had a lot already.

313
00:18:12,533 --> 00:18:13,967
Come on, I'll take you
to your room.

314
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:15,467
Paolo!

315
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,800
Marj!

316
00:18:19,267 --> 00:18:20,033
<i> Marj!</i>

317
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,300
Edward. Hello?

318
00:18:23,467 --> 00:18:26,167
Edward, your brother's taking me
to my room.

319
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:27,700
Oh, okay, okay.

320
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,867
<i> Bye!</i>

321
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:32,033
Wait, wait! Marj!

322
00:18:35,267 --> 00:18:36,233
I'll get your bag,
just a minute.

323
00:18:36,367 --> 00:18:37,600
Just stay there.

324
00:18:39,267 --> 00:18:41,133
Here's your bag.

325
00:18:47,467 --> 00:18:50,467
Oh no!

326
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:51,800
The key.

327
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,533
- We'll figure it out.
- It's gone.

328
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:55,967
Come on, we'll figure it out.

329
00:18:56,100 --> 00:18:58,033
The key's missing!

330
00:19:01,133 --> 00:19:02,633
Okay.

331
00:19:02,767 --> 00:19:04,400
Hold on, I still want to drink.

332
00:19:04,533 --> 00:19:06,367
It's over,
we're done drinking, Slowly.

333
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:08,167
It's done, oh, here.

334
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:09,533
- Ah.
- Careful.

335
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:15,833
I'm taking
your jacket off, okay?

336
00:19:15,967 --> 00:19:18,167
You're being naughty.

337
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:19,300
What do you mean by naughty?

338
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:22,200
Look at you,
you're soaked in sweat.

339
00:19:22,867 --> 00:19:24,233
You drank way too much.

340
00:19:24,367 --> 00:19:26,500
You told me to drink.

341
00:19:31,233 --> 00:19:32,467
It's hot.

342
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:37,733
I'm proud of you.

343
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:44,267
How could I not be sweating...

344
00:19:45,433 --> 00:19:48,133
when you're staring
at me like that?

345
00:19:52,133 --> 00:19:54,133
It's because I think
you're beautiful.

346
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:14,467
Sorry.

347
00:20:15,733 --> 00:20:16,600
Why?

348
00:20:16,733 --> 00:20:18,633
Sorry, I shouldn't have
done that.

349
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:20,667
You're drunk.

350
00:20:24,567 --> 00:20:26,833
I know what I'm doing.

351
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:35,133
You told me to let loose.

352
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:39,600
To let everything out.

353
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:43,200
I just want to...

354
00:20:45,267 --> 00:20:47,967
I just want to lose control
right now.

355
00:20:49,367 --> 00:20:50,233
Just...

356
00:20:50,367 --> 00:20:51,867
Just for now.

357
00:20:52,967 --> 00:20:57,467
To be free from
all the emotions and guilt.

358
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:00,000
Just for now.

359
00:22:03,233 --> 00:22:05,000
<i> Darn it.</i>

360
00:22:05,133 --> 00:22:06,933
This is embarrassing!

361
00:22:36,300 --> 00:22:37,400
Edward?

362
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,800
Why didn't you join us
for breakfast earlier?

363
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:43,767
Is everything all right?

364
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:47,267
I'm worried, Mom.

365
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:50,267
I feel like...

366
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:53,900
Paolo's taking advantage
of Marj.

367
00:22:59,233 --> 00:23:00,533
Son...

368
00:23:00,667 --> 00:23:03,300
you might be overthinking.

369
00:23:03,433 --> 00:23:05,700
I don't think your brother
would actually do that.

370
00:23:05,833 --> 00:23:07,967
He knows you like Marj, right?

371
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:09,233
Yes, Mom.

372
00:23:09,367 --> 00:23:11,533
When did that ever stop Paolo?

373
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:16,767
Edward, why don't you
just give your brother

374
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:19,033
the benefit of the doubt?

375
00:23:19,167 --> 00:23:20,600
And focus instead

376
00:23:20,733 --> 00:23:24,067
on how you're going to court
Marj when they get back.

377
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:49,667
Marj?

378
00:23:51,367 --> 00:23:52,600
Marj?

379
00:24:01,533 --> 00:24:02,700
Marj?

380
00:24:39,267 --> 00:24:41,233
What did you do, Marj?

381
00:24:44,633 --> 00:24:46,533
Nothing.

382
00:24:47,567 --> 00:24:48,833
It didn't mean anything.

383
00:24:48,967 --> 00:24:50,000
It was nothing.

384
00:24:51,667 --> 00:24:52,800
Nothing.

385
00:24:57,733 --> 00:24:58,567
Ah, I don't know.

386
00:24:58,700 --> 00:25:00,400
I don't know about you.

387
00:25:01,433 --> 00:25:03,267
I don't know about you, girl.

388
00:25:03,433 --> 00:25:05,000
I don't know
what to make of you.

389
00:25:05,133 --> 00:25:06,300
Do you have a hangover?

390
00:25:08,767 --> 00:25:10,733
Yes. My head hurts.

391
00:25:15,567 --> 00:25:18,700
Sorry, is my headache
funny to you?

392
00:25:18,833 --> 00:25:20,433
No, no.

393
00:25:20,567 --> 00:25:21,967
It's just that,

394
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:24,000
It's my first time having
experienced "sex and run".

395
00:25:24,133 --> 00:25:25,967
So that's what
it feels like, huh?

396
00:25:26,100 --> 00:25:27,833
But, at least,
you're still here.

397
00:25:32,233 --> 00:25:33,267
Just kidding.

398
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,300
Don't worry.

399
00:25:36,433 --> 00:25:38,133
You don't have to take
responsibility.

400
00:25:39,267 --> 00:25:40,900
I wanted what we did.

401
00:25:41,033 --> 00:25:42,500
But don't worry,

402
00:25:42,633 --> 00:25:45,000
just forget what happened, okay?

403
00:25:45,133 --> 00:25:46,733
That we had sex?

404
00:25:48,500 --> 00:25:50,300
Okay, okay.

405
00:25:51,300 --> 00:25:52,700
I'll stop joking about it.

406
00:25:53,300 --> 00:25:55,467
I'll forget what happened
between us.

407
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:56,800
Just like you want.

408
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:10,733
Hello, Hannah?

409
00:26:10,867 --> 00:26:12,400
Marj, it's about your mom.

410
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,633
She left last night,
and she still hasn't come back.

411
00:26:14,767 --> 00:26:15,367
I can't reach her.

412
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:17,367
I'm really worried!

413
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:19,267
Hannah, wait.

414
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:20,133
Hold on, hold on.

415
00:26:20,267 --> 00:26:21,833
I don't understand.

416
00:26:21,967 --> 00:26:23,333
Breathe, okay?

417
00:26:23,467 --> 00:26:25,067
What happened?

418
00:26:27,300 --> 00:26:28,833
She left last night

419
00:26:28,967 --> 00:26:30,900
and hasn't returned.

420
00:26:31,033 --> 00:26:32,767
<i> I'm really worried!</i>

421
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:34,867
What? Where did Mom go?

422
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,200
I don't know,
when I got home,

423
00:26:36,333 --> 00:26:37,200
she was gone.

424
00:26:37,333 --> 00:26:38,600
Jobert didn't even sleep.

425
00:26:38,733 --> 00:26:39,933
He's been waiting for her.

426
00:26:41,133 --> 00:26:44,200
Has she replied to any messages?

427
00:26:44,367 --> 00:26:46,200
No!

428
00:26:49,667 --> 00:26:50,467
I was calling you last night,

429
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:51,400
You didn't answer.

430
00:26:51,533 --> 00:26:53,000
When I talked to Marj,
she was drunk.

431
00:26:53,133 --> 00:26:54,600
And then what?
You undressed her?

432
00:26:54,733 --> 00:26:55,467
Laid her down?

433
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:56,200
Kissed her?

434
00:26:56,367 --> 00:26:57,433
Good job, Paolo.

435
00:26:57,567 --> 00:26:59,933
That's the kind of woman
you should be dating, son.

436
00:27:00,067 --> 00:27:01,167
What? He told you that?

437
00:27:01,300 --> 00:27:02,267
Yes, he did.

438
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:03,900
I don't get impressed easily.

439
00:27:04,033 --> 00:27:05,333
My standards are high.

440
00:27:05,467 --> 00:27:07,067
But Marj?

441
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,000
She's approved in my book.

442
00:27:08,133 --> 00:27:09,700
You told me you didn't like her!

443
00:27:09,833 --> 00:27:10,767
That I should go for her!

444
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:12,033
I felt so betrayed.

445
00:27:12,167 --> 00:27:14,400
Because Paolo knew I liked you.
